Decentralized Legal Contract L1 Overview

Decentralized Legal Contract L1 provides a blockchain-based infrastructure for creating, executing, and enforcing legal agreements through smart contracts.

Features

On-chain legal agreements

Automated contract execution

Transparent contract terms

Dispute resolution mechanisms

Tamper-proof legal records

Architecture Contract Registry

Stores legal agreements and metadata.

Execution Engine

Automates contract conditions and triggers.

Dispute Resolution Module

Handles arbitration and conflict management.

Verification Layer

Ensures authenticity of participants.

Use Cases

Digital legal agreements

Freelance contracts

Business partnerships

Cross-border transactions
